# Icons & assets

How to use images, UI icons, and SVGs in this template. Not file-naming rules — see `naming-conventions.mdc` for kebab-case under `src/assets/`. Icon **colors** follow `design-tokens.mdc` (semantic tokens, not arbitrary fills).

## UI icons

- Use the shadcn preset’s `iconLibrary` in `components.json` (`lucide`, `tabler`, `phosphor`, etc.). Set via [shadcn Create](https://ui.shadcn.com/create) or `apply` on a preset.
- Import from that library in components. **Do not** hand-write inline `<svg>` for standard glyphs (chevrons, close, menu, etc.).
- Prefer **direct imports** from the icon package over heavy barrel entry points when bundle size matters (see `naming-conventions.mdc`).

## Brand / social logos

- Use [thesvg](https://github.com/GLINCKER/thesvg) (`npm i thesvg`): tree-shakeable, typed brand icons.
- **Do not** paste one-off brand SVG markup.

## Static assets (`src/assets/`)

- **File names:** kebab-case (e.g. `logo-dark.svg`).
- Use only when the icon library or thesvg cannot cover the use case — illustrations, custom artwork, non-brand imagery.

## No custom inline SVG icons

- Do not generate ad-hoc `<svg>` in components. Agents often produce inconsistent paths, wrong viewBox, or non-accessible markup.
- Use the preset icon library or thesvg; reserve `src/assets/` for assets that are not in those packages.
